9 Section 2. KRS 271B.7-400 is amended to read as follows:
10 (1) A person shall not commence a proceeding in the right of a domestic or foreign
11 corporation unless he or she was a shareholder of the corporation when the
12 transaction complained of occurred or unless he or she became a shareholder
13 through transfer by operation of law from one who was a shareholder at that time.
14 The derivative proceeding shall not be maintained if it appears that the person
15 commencing the proceeding does not fairly and adequately represent the interests of
16 the shareholders in enforcing the right of the corporation.
17 (2) A complaint in a proceeding brought in the right of a corporation shall be verified
18 and allege with particularity the demand made, if any, to obtain action by the board
19 of directors and either that the demand was refused or ignored or why he or she did
20 not make the demand. Whether or not a demand for action was made, if the
21 corporation commences an investigation of the charges made in the demand or
22 complaint, the court may stay any proceeding until the investigation is completed.
23 (3) A proceeding commenced under this section may not be discontinued or settled
24 without the court's approval. If the court determines that a proposed discontinuance
25 or settlement will substantially affect the interest of the corporation's shareholders
26 or a class of shareholders, the court shall direct that notice be given the shareholders
27 affected.
